    <note type="biography">
        <p>German-born palaeontologist, physician, and botanist. Studied at Tübingen, Göttingen, and Basel; MD 1868. Practised medicine in Italy from about 1872 and also pursued his study of palaeontology and botany. Travelled and collected in Samos, 1886–9. Worked for the British Museum, 1892–1908; travelled and collected in Madagascar, 1894–6. FRS 1908.</p></note>
